5|$|For Washington is a 1911 American silent short <b>historical</b> <b>fiction</b> drama film {{produced}} by the Thanhouser Company. The film is a fictional account of how a patriotic maid's home is taken over by Hessian officers in the American Revolutionary War. She hides her hatred of them and plies them with drink before delivering a message to George Washington. She leads them in crossing of the Delaware River and the historic capture. The film's crossing scene was inspired by Emmanuel Leutze's Washington Crossing the Delaware. The film was praised by critics, but {{the notion that the}} film was purely a <b>historical</b> <b>fiction</b> was lost on some. The film is presumed lost.|$|E
