5|$|Walpole's output {{was large}} and varied. Between 1909 and 1941 he wrote thirty-six novels, five volumes of short stories, two {{original}} plays and three volumes of memoirs. His range included disturbing studies of the macabre, children's stories and <b>historical</b> <b>fiction,</b> most notably his Herries Chronicle series, set in the Lake District. He worked in Hollywood writing scenarios for two Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer films in the 1930s, and played a cameo in the 1935 version of David Copperfield.|$|E
